<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-29T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-29T13:36:00-05:00" n="669" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d669">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/503: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-29T12:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">August
                                            29, 1920—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 11:28
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>125. Herrera overwhelmingly elected in a fair and quiet election. He
                                received above 225,000 votes against 6,800 for Castillo and 5,300
                                for Fuentes. The official vote will not change these figures very
                                materially.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>